  "a0A0B3CC0-EC16-E580-4CFE-41C08F94888C": {
    "parent": "a9D0D3139-A108-E5E1-2AC8-E85A8F1D57CB",
    "id": "0",
    "title": "DAX Studio",
    "type": "text",
    "completed": false,
    "text": "<p>DAX Studio is a great, free, open-source tool that offers you many functionalities to simplify the development of Power BI and Tabular models. This part of the DAX Tools video course is a comprehensive guide to the features of DAX Studio. It is also good to watch if you are already using DAX Studio in your day-to-day work: you might have missed one of the many opportunities that DAX Studio offers you to make your job easier.</p>\r\n<p>By following the video lectures, you learn all the features of DAX Studio: from simple functionalities – like running a query – to the most advanced about performance analysis.</p>\r\n<p>In the beginning, you can follow the lectures in the recommended sequence. You may then want to refer to the lectures at a later time, when you want to review a specific feature.</p>\r\n<p>You can download the latest version of DAX Studio at <a href=\"https://daxstudio.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://daxstudio.org</a></p>\r\n<p>Below you can download the sample files used in the lectures.</p>\r\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: The \"Query Builder\" feature shown in the lectures might be still in preview in DAX Studio. You can enable it in File / Options / Advanced / Preview Features.</p>",
    "video": "",
    "duration": 0,
    "nop": false,
    "files": [
      {
        "title": "DAX Studio - demo files",
        "url": "https://mysqlbi.blob.core.windows.net/daxtools/DAX Studio - demo files.zip?sv=2016-05-31&se=2023-06-11T17%3A51%3A55Z&sr=b&sp=r&spr=https&sig=HwY2uLuS%2Fx0iUB4q6LZT9fv3L%2BGm%2Fd5X9a17DRCz5jE%3D",
