  "aA8C447FA-BAC4-DC8A-B045-2A3E778A4D6A": {
    "parent": "aC9583909-9725-2BE4-3B83-5420A4513A2D",
    "id": "20",
    "title": "Analyze in Excel for Power BI Desktop",
    "type": "text",
    "completed": false,
    "text": "<p>Analyze in Excel is a free, open-source add-in for Power BI Desktop. It opens an Excel file that is connected with the Power BI Desktop file that is currently open.</p>\r\n<p>In this short training, we demonstrate not only how to use the tool (that part is just one click) but also how and when it is good to rely on Excel as a client tool: for example when you need to trace MDX queries sent from Excel to Power BI Desktop.</p>\r\n<p>Download the latest version of Analyze in Excel at <a href=\"https://www.sqlbi.com/tools/analyze-in-excel-for-power-bi-desktop/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://www.sqlbi.com/tools/analyze-in-excel-for-power-bi-desktop/</a></p>\r\n<p>Below you can download the sample files used in the lectures.</p>",
    "video": "",
